---
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang='en'>
  <head>
    <meta charset='UTF-8' />
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0' />
    <meta name='description' content='Guillermo Laporta is a Spanish flutist, composer, designer and multimedia artist based between New York City and Asturias, Spain.' />
    <title>Guillermo Laporta - Flutist, Composer, Designer</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #08090b;
        --paper: #f3ede3;
        --text: #f3ede3;
        --muted: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.72);
        --line: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.16);
        --soft: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.06);
        --accent: #cba56a;
        --dark: #08090b;
        --max: 1180px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--text);
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(203, 165, 106, 0.2), transparent 36rem),
          radial-gradient(circle at 85% 10%, rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.08), transparent 30rem),
          linear-gradient(135deg, #060709 0%, #111216 48%, #050506 100%);
        font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, sans-serif;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
      }

      .site-header {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0 0 auto 0;
        z-index: 50;
        background: rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.72);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
        backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
      }

      .nav {
        width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 32px));
        min-height: 68px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 24px;
      }

      .brand {
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-weight: 800;
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 18px;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      .nav-links a:hover {
        color: var(--text);
      }

      .hero {
        width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 32px));
        min-height: 100svh;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 140px 0 80px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(330px, 0.95fr);
        gap: 56px;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 12px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 0.76rem;
        font-weight: 800;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.19em;
      }

      .eyebrow::before {
        content: '';
        width: 32px;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--accent);
      }

      h1 {
        max-width: 860px;
        margin: 22px 0 20px;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-size: clamp(4rem, 11vw, 10rem);
        line-height: 0.83;
        letter-spacing: -0.08em;
        font-weight: 400;
      }

      .hero-subtitle {
        max-width: 720px;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: clamp(1.12rem, 2vw, 1.55rem);
        line-height: 1.45;
      }

      .hero-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 12px;
        margin-top: 34px;
      }

      .button {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 0 18px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.05);
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        transition: transform 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
      }

      .button.primary {
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--dark);
        border-color: var(--paper);
      }

      .button:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
        background: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.1);
      }

      .button.primary:hover {
        background: #ffffff;
      }

      .hero-card {
        min-height: 640px;
        border-radius: 34px;
        overflow: hidden;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: #15161a;
        position: relative;
        box-shadow: 0 40px 120px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.48);
      }

      .hero-card img {
        filter: saturate(0.92) contrast(1.08);
      }

      .hero-card::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.05), rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.82)),
          linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.22), transparent 45%);
      }

      .hero-card-caption {
        position: absolute;
        z-index: 2;
        left: 28px;
        right: 28px;
        bottom: 28px;
        color: var(--paper);
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: end;
      }

      .hero-card-caption strong {
        display: block;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4.5rem);
        line-height: 0.92;
        letter-spacing: -0.06em;
        font-weight: 400;
      }

      .hero-card-caption span {
        color: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.76);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        max-width: 180px;
        text-align: right;
      }

      main {
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      section {
        width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 32px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 92px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      .section-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.34fr 0.66fr;
        gap: 58px;
      }

      .section-label {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        font-size: 0.76rem;
        font-weight: 900;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        letter-spacing: -0.055em;
        font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 6vw, 5.7rem);
        line-height: 0.94;
      }

      .lead {
        margin: 24px 0 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: clamp(1.08rem, 1.7vw, 1.34rem);
        line-height: 1.62;
      }

      .text-block p {
        margin: 0 0 22px;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.78;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
      }

      .stats {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 12px;
        margin-top: 34px;
      }

      .stat {
        padding: 22px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 24px;
        background: var(--soft);
      }

      .stat strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 2.1rem;
      }

      .stat span {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.88rem;
      }

      .image-strip {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr 1fr;
        gap: 14px;
        margin-top: 42px;
      }

      .image-strip figure {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 330px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 28px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--soft);
        position: relative;
      }

      .image-strip figure:nth-child(2) {
        transform: translateY(38px);
      }

      .image-strip figcaption {
        position: absolute;
        left: 16px;
        right: 16px;
        bottom: 16px;
        padding: 12px 14px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.18);
        border-radius: 16px;
        background: rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.58);
        backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        color: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.82);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
      }

      .cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 14px;
      }

      .card {
        min-height: 260px;
        padding: 24px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 26px;
        background: var(--soft);
      }

      .card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        line-height: 1;
      }

      .card .meta {
        margin-bottom: 22px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        line-height: 1.35;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      .card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.62;
      }

      .split-feature {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.95fr 1.05fr;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      .feature-image {
        min-height: 560px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 32px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--soft);
      }

      .feature-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .feature-row {
        padding: 22px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 24px;
        background: rgba(243, 237, 227, 0.045);
      }

      .feature-row h3 {
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-size: 1.55rem;
        font-weight: 400;
        letter-spacing: -0.035em;
      }

      .feature-row p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.58;
      }

      .project-links {
        display: grid;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .project-link {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.75fr 1.25fr auto;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 22px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 24px;
        background: var(--soft);
      }

      .project-link strong {
        font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 1.7rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      .project-link span {
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      .project-link em {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-style: normal;
      }

      .press-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .quote {
        min-height: 170px;
        padding: 18px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 22px;
        background: rgba(203, 165, 106, 0.08);
      }

      .quote strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      .quote span {
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.5;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }

      .contact-panel {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      .contact-card {
        padding: 32px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 30px;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--dark);
      }

      .contact-card h2 {
        color: var(--dark);
      }

      .contact-card p {
        color: rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.7);
        line-height: 1.65;
      }

      .contact-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-top: 24px;
      }

      .contact-links a {
        border: 1px solid rgba(8, 9, 11, 0.16);
        border-radius: 999px;
        padding: 12px 14px;
        color: var(--dark);
      }

      .contact-image {
        min-height: 420px;
        border-radius: 30px;
        overflow: hidden;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      footer {
        width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 32px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 34px 0 46px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 20px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 920px) {
        .nav-links {
          display: none;
        }

        .hero,
        .section-grid,
        .split-feature,
        .contact-panel {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .hero {
          padding-top: 118px;
          gap: 36px;
        }

        .hero-card {
          min-height: 520px;
        }

        .stats,
        .cards,
        .press-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }

        .image-strip {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .image-strip figure:nth-child(2) {
          transform: none;
        }

        .project-link {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 560px) {
        .hero-card,
        .feature-image,
        .contact-image {
          min-height: 390px;
        }

        section {
          padding: 70px 0;
        }

        .stats,
        .cards,
        .press-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        footer {
          flex-direction: column;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class='site-header'>
      <nav class='nav' aria-label='Main navigation'>
        <a class='brand' href='#top'>Guillermo Laporta</a>
        <div class='nav-links'>
          <a href='#about'>About</a>
          <a href='#work'>Work</a>
          <a href='#projects'>Projects</a>
          <a href='#press'>Press</a>
          <a href='#contact'>Contact</a>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id='top'>
      <section class='hero' aria-label='Introduction'>
        <div>
          <div class='eyebrow'>Flutist / Composer / Designer</div>
          <h1>Guillermo Laporta</h1>
          <p class='hero-subtitle'>Spanish flutist, composer, stage designer and multimedia artist based between New York City and Asturias, Spain. His work connects music, image, theater, dance, video and place.</p>
          <div class='hero-actions'>
            <a class='button primary' href='#work'>Explore selected work</a>
            <a class='button' href='#contact'>Contact</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class='hero-card'>
          <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/about-guillermo@2x.png' alt='Portrait of Guillermo Laporta' />
          <figcaption class='hero-card-caption'>
            <strong>music / image / space</strong>
            <span>Performance as a visual and spatial experience.</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section id='about'>
        <div class='section-grid'>
          <div class='section-label'>About</div>
          <div>
            <h2>A practice built between sound, image and place.</h2>
            <p class='lead'>Laporta works across performance, composition, dramaturgy and stage design. At the center of his artistic practice is the visual concert, a way of presenting classical and contemporary music through light, projection, spatial design and theatrical thinking while preserving the integrity of the score.</p>
            <div class='stats'>
              <div class='stat'><strong>NYC</strong><span>Creative base</span></div>
              <div class='stat'><strong>Asturias</strong><span>Rural arts work</span></div>
              <div class='stat'><strong>3</strong><span>Studio albums</span></div>
              <div class='stat'><strong>2013</strong><span>CreArtBox founded</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class='image-strip' aria-label='Selected images'>
          <figure>
            <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/_DSC03402.jpg' alt='Guillermo Laporta performing' loading='lazy' />
            <figcaption>Performance and chamber music</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/visuality01.jpg' alt='Visual concert stage image' loading='lazy' />
            <figcaption>Visual concert design</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/venue-festival.jpg' alt='Rural festival venue' loading='lazy' />
            <figcaption>Artistic work in rural spaces</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='work'>
        <div class='section-grid'>
          <div class='section-label'>Selected work</div>
          <div>
            <h2>Opera, ballet, chamber music and visual performance.</h2>
            <p class='lead'>His projects often begin with live music and expand into layered theatrical environments: moving images, projection, lighting, choreography and scenography.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class='cards' style='margin-top:42px'>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>Architecture of a Common Man</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Opera / ballet / film - 2023</div>
            <p>Music, dramaturgy, libretto and screenplay for a staged work combining live performance, cinema and movement.</p>
          </article>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>Fragile Form</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Visual concert trilogy - 2022</div>
            <p>Concept and design for Equilibrium, Rupture and Metamorphosis, an immersive project about fragility, matter and transformation.</p>
          </article>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>Queens Preludes</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Multimedia chamber work - 2021</div>
            <p>Music for flute and piano presented as a multimedia concert in New York, Madrid and Tokyo.</p>
          </article>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>Two Roads</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Opera and ballet - 2019</div>
            <p>Music, dramaturgy and libretto for a stage work exploring choice, memory and the paths that shape a life.</p>
          </article>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>AWAVE</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Album and video performance - 2018-2020</div>
            <p>A collection of works for flute, piano, electronics and video inspired by travel, landscape and motion.</p>
          </article>
          <article class='card'>
            <h3>Visuality</h3>
            <div class='meta'>Concert theater - 2014-2016</div>
            <p>A concert-theater production merging live classical music, visual art and technology.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='practice'>
        <div class='split-feature'>
          <figure class='feature-image'>
            <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/Two%20Roads,%20Opera%20dance%20by%20Guillermo%20Laporta%2007.jpg' alt='Two Roads stage production by Guillermo Laporta' loading='lazy' />
          </figure>
          <div class='feature-list'>
            <div class='section-label'>Artistic practice</div>
            <div class='feature-row'>
              <h3>Flute and chamber music</h3>
              <p>Laporta has performed symphonic, opera and chamber repertoire in Europe, Japan and the United States, including appearances connected to Carnegie Hall and Lincoln Center.</p>
            </div>
            <div class='feature-row'>
              <h3>Composition and transcription</h3>
              <p>He develops new flute repertoire through original compositions, arrangements and chamber versions of works originally written for other instrumental forces.</p>
            </div>
            <div class='feature-row'>
              <h3>Stage and visual design</h3>
              <p>His productions use lighting, projection and spatial design as musical partners, creating environments where image and sound shape one dramaturgical arc.</p>
            </div>
            <div class='feature-row'>
              <h3>Rural cultural projects</h3>
              <p>Through Festival ADAR, he develops itinerant artistic experiences in rural Asturias, activating heritage spaces, landscapes and local communities through music and visual creation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='projects'>
        <div class='section-grid'>
          <div class='section-label'>Projects</div>
          <div>
            <h2>Platforms for creation and performance.</h2>
            <p class='lead'>These projects are part of Laporta's broader artistic ecosystem. The personal practice remains the center: music, design, performance and cultural imagination.</p>
            <div class='project-links' style='margin-top:38px'>
              <a class='project-link' href='https://creartbox.nyc' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>
                <strong>CreArtBox</strong>
                <span>A New York based chamber music and multimedia ensemble co-founded by Guillermo Laporta and Josefina Urraca.</span>
                <em>Visit</em>
              </a>
              <a class='project-link' href='https://festivaladar.com' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>
                <strong>Festival ADAR</strong>
                <span>An itinerant arts festival and residency project rooted in rural Asturias, Spain.</span>
                <em>Visit</em>
              </a>
              <a class='project-link' href='https://play.creartbox.nyc' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>
                <strong>Digital Concert Hall</strong>
                <span>A digital archive of performances, chamber works and visual concert projects.</span>
                <em>Watch</em>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='recordings'>
        <div class='section-grid'>
          <div class='section-label'>Recordings</div>
          <div>
            <h2>Flute repertoire, albums and chamber versions.</h2>
            <p class='lead'>Laporta's recording work includes original pieces, chamber arrangements and repertoire for flute with piano, strings, harp and electronics.</p>
            <div class='feature-list' style='margin-top:36px'>
              <div class='feature-row'><h3>Debussy & Respighi Violin Sonatas</h3><p>Arrangements and recordings that bring violin repertoire into the flute chamber music world.</p></div>
              <div class='feature-row'><h3>AWAVE</h3><p>Original music for flute, piano, electronics and video.</p></div>
              <div class='feature-row'><h3>12 Preludes</h3><p>Original pieces for flute and piano connected to memory, image and travel.</p></div>
              <div class='feature-row'><h3>Chamber versions</h3><p>Live chamber arrangements and performances of works by Granados, Mahler, Bach, Haydn and others.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='press'>
        <div class='section-grid'>
          <div class='section-label'>Press</div>
          <div>
            <h2>Recognition and critical response.</h2>
            <p class='lead'>Laporta's work and the projects he has built have been described through their distinctive combination of music, staging, visual design and multidisciplinary performance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class='press-grid' style='margin-top:40px'>
          <div class='quote'><strong>The New Yorker</strong><span>Art and music top picks.</span></div>
          <div class='quote'><strong>Time Out</strong><span>A new ensemble devoted to multidisciplinary events.</span></div>
          <div class='quote'><strong>El Pais</strong><span>A striking staging.</span></div>
          <div class='quote'><strong>Times Ledger</strong><span>A unique take on classical music.</span></div>
          <div class='quote'><strong>Broadway World</strong><span>Visually and aurally compelling.</span></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id='contact'>
        <div class='contact-panel'>
          <div class='contact-card'>
            <div class='section-label' style='color:#8d6b37'>Contact</div>
            <h2>Performances, commissions and collaborations.</h2>
            <p>For concerts, visual concert projects, commissions, media requests or artistic collaborations, please get in touch.</p>
            <div class='contact-links'>
              <a href='mailto:info@creartbox.nyc'>info@creartbox.nyc</a>
              <a href='https://creartbox.nyc/pages/guillermo-laporta' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Extended bio</a>
              <a href='https://www.instagram.com/creartbox' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Instagram</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <figure class='contact-image'>
            <img src='https://www.media.creartbox.nyc/_DSC0409.jpg' alt='Guillermo Laporta portrait and performance image' loading='lazy' />
